# shadcn/ui Components

This project uses shadcn/ui exclusively for all UI elements.

- Only use shadcn/ui components and patterns for UI in this project.
- Do not create custom UI primitives, custom-styled buttons, custom dialogs, custom forms, or one-off visual components.
- If a needed UI component is not installed, add the matching shadcn/ui component instead of building a custom replacement.
- If shadcn/ui does not provide an exact component, compose existing shadcn/ui components before considering any other approach.
- All Clerk sign-in and sign-up triggers must use the shadcn/ui `Button` component.
- Clerk sign-in and sign-up flows must open in a modal. Do not navigate directly to standalone Clerk auth pages unless the user explicitly requests a route-based auth page.
- If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project, initialize it with:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

- If a needed component is not installed, add it with:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component>
```

For example, to install the button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```
